  - pytorch
  - deep learning
abstract: >
  QPP (Quantile Piecewise Perceptron) is a novel parametric compression technique
  that reduces the number of parameters in neural network weight matrices rather
  than just their bit precision. When perceptron weights are sorted, they form a
  smooth monotonic quantile curve that can be approximated with a linear interpolation
  basis of K anchors plus block-shared ordering. Combined with 2-bit codebook
  quantization over anchors and INT8 for incompatible layers, QPP achieves 41.1%
  compression on Qwen3-4B with coherent generation, and is 7× more effective than
  GGUF Q4_K_M on attention layers where it applies.
